# Ninja Connect

[![Supported Python Versions](https://img.shields.io/pypi/pyversions/rich/13.2.0)](https://pypi.org/project/rich/)\
[![PyPI version](https://badge.fury.io/py/ninjaconnect.svg)](https://badge.fury.io/py/ninjaconnect)

NinjaConnect is a Python package designed to facilitate the connection to the WireGuard VPN command-line interface (CLI) based package. This package enables users to establish a connection between their devices and their our laboratory environments using straightforward and simple commands. In essence, NinjaConnect streamlines the process of connecting your device to your lab through the WireGuard VPN, making it more user-friendly and accessible.

# Installation

Installation of NinjaConnect is straightforward and can be accomplished using Python in any Linux environment with the following simple command

```
pip install ninjaconnect
```
## Command and Steps
# Step 1 :
```
ninja configure
```

![configure](https://i.imgur.com/atCGkeG.png)
# Step 2 :
```
ninja login
```

![logingit](https://i.imgur.com/eLlxzk0.png)
# Step 3 :
```
ninja add_device
```
![adddevice](https://i.imgur.com/LstuXGA.png)


# Step 4
```
ninja connect
```

![connect](https://i.imgur.com/ofoa59k.png)

Now all its ok you can now able to ping and ssh you labs IP

# Step 6
After the you work completed you can disconnect

```
ninja disconnect
```
![disconnect](https://i.imgur.com/BpEffjl.png)
# Step 7
For logout use 

```
ninja logout
```
![logout](https://i.imgur.com/ceiUmCl.png)

